Description: ROCpAIv2 provides a unified framework for computing and comparing
    standardized partial area under the ROC curve (pAUC) in the evaluation of
    binary classifiers, particularly in restricted regions of clinical interest.
    The package implements four scaled indexes tailored to different ROC curve
    behaviours: MCpAUC (McClish 1989), TpAUC (Vivo et al. 2018), NpAUC
    (Jiang et al. 1996) for the high-specificity and high-sensitivity domains,
    and FpAUC (Franco and Vivo 2021) for any curve shape, including improper
    ROC curves. All indexes are supported by nonparametric bootstrap confidence
    intervals. ROCpAIv2 accepts both data.frame and SummarizedExperiment inputs,
    returns results as tibble or SummarizedExperiment, and produces
    publication-quality ROC curve plots with shaded partial-area regions. It is
    designed for full compatibility with Bioconductor pipelines, making it
    suitable for high-throughput biomarker discovery applications.
